### English Title:
A Moving Photo of a Palestinian Child Who Lost Both Arms in an Israeli Airstrike Wins Photojournalism Award of the Year

### English Text Summary:
A poignant photograph of a Palestinian child, Mahmoud Ajour, who lost both arms in an Israeli airstrike in Gaza, has won the Photo of the Year award. Photographer Samar Abu Al-Aouf, also from Gaza, captured the image three months after the incident, which left Mahmoud with one arm amputated and the other severely injured. The child and his family were evacuated to Doha, Qatar, for medical treatment. The photo serves as a stark reminder of the long-term consequences of war in Gaza, which has resulted in significant casualties and displacement. The award highlights themes of conflict, migration, and resilience, with the winning image selected from nearly 60,000 submissions.

